A N A C T
RELATING TO FOOD AND DRUGS -- UNIFORM CONTROLLED SUBSTANCES ACT --
OFFENSES AND PENALTIES
Introduced By: Representatives Hopkins, Place, Roberts, J. Brien, Bennett, Perez,
Corvese, and Chippendale
Date Introduced: February 28, 2025
Referred To: House Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Sections 21-28-4.1.1 and 21-28-4.1.2 of the General Laws in Chapter 21-28
2 entitled "Uniform Controlled Substances Act" are hereby amended to read as follows:
3 21-28-4.01.1. Certain quantities of controlled substances.
4 (a) Except as authorized by this chapter, it shall be unlawful for any person to manufacture,
5 sell, or possess with intent to manufacture or sell, a controlled substance classified in schedule I or
6 II (excluding marijuana) or to possess or deliver the following enumerated quantities of certain
7 controlled substances:
8 (1) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of a mixture or substance containing a
9 detectable amount of heroin;
10 (2) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of a mixture or substance containing a
11 detectable amount of:
12 (i) Coca leaves, except coca leaves and extracts of coca leaves from which cocaine,
13 ecgonine, and derivatives of ecgonine or their salts have been removed;
14 (ii) Cocaine, its salts, optical and geometric isomers, and salts of isomers;
15 (iii) Ecgonine, its derivatives, their salts, isomers, and salts of isomers; or
16 (iv) Any compound, mixture, or preparation that contains any quantity of any of the
17 substances referred to in paragraphs (i) — (iii) of this subdivision;
18 (3) One gram (1 g.) to ten grams (10 gs.) of phencyclidine (PCP) or one hundred (100) to

1 one thousand (1,000) tablets of a mixture or substance containing a detectable amount of
2 phencyclidine (PCP);
3 (4) One-tenth of a gram (0.1 g.) to one gram (1 g.) of lysergic acid diethylamide (LSD) or
4 one hundred (100) to one thousand (1,000) tablets of a mixture or substance containing a detectable
5 amount of lysergic acid diethylamide (LSD);
6 (5) One kilogram (1 kg.) to five kilograms (5 kgs.) of a mixture containing a detectable
7 amount of marijuana;
8 (6) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of a mixture or substance containing a
9 detectable amount of synthetic drugs; or
10 (7) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of a mixture or substance containing a
11 detectable amount at least ten percent (10%) of fentanyl or its analogs, including, but not limited
12 to: N-(1-phenethylpiperidin-4-yl)-N-phenylacetamide, its optical, positional, and geometric
13 isomers, salts, and salts of isomers (acetyl fentanyl); N-(1-phenethylpiperidin-4-yl)-N-phenylfuran-
14 2carboxamide (furanyl fentanyl); and N-Phenethyl-4-piperidinone (4-AN-PP); or
15 (8) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of a mixture or substance containing a
16 detectable amount of carfentanil; or
17 (9) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of 3,4-methyl-enedioxymethamphetamine
18 (MDMA), its optical, positional, and geometric isomers, salts, and salts of isomers; or
19 (10) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of amphetamine, its salts, optical isomers,
20 and salts of its optical isomers; or
21 (11) One ounce (1 oz.) to one kilogram (1 kg.) of methamphetamine, its salts, and salts of
22 its isomers.
23 (b) Any person who violates this section shall be guilty of a crime, and upon conviction,
24 may be imprisoned for a term up to fifty (50) years and fined not more than five hundred thousand
25 dollars ($500,000).
26 21-28-4.01.2. Certain quantities of controlled substances.
27 (a) Except as authorized by the chapter, it shall be unlawful for any person to possess,
28 manufacture, sell, or deliver the following enumerated quantities of certain controlled substances:
29 (1) More than one kilogram (1 kg.) of a mixture or substance containing a detectable
30 amount of heroin;
31 (2) More than one kilogram (1 kg.) of a mixture or substance containing a detectable
32 amount of:
33 (i) Coca leaves, except coca leaves and extracts of coca leaves from which cocaine,
34 ecgonine, and derivatives of ecgonine or their salts have been removed;
